To make the FAQ index a conditional **addendum** to the sidebar, you can dynamically append the FAQ section to the sidebar while ensuring the rest of the sidebar remains intact. Here's how:

### Updated Example Code:

```javascript
import { createSignal } from "solid-js";

function App() {
  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = createSignal("Home");

  const faqIndex = [
    "What is this site about?",
    "How can I contact support?",
    "Where can I find more information?",
  ];

  return (
    <div style={{ display: "flex" }}>
      {/* Sidebar */}
      <aside style={{ width: "200px", borderRight: "1px solid #ccc", padding: "16px" }}>
        <ul>
          <li onClick={() => setActiveTab("Home")}>Home</li>
          <li onClick={() => setActiveTab("FAQ")}>FAQ</li>
          <li onClick={() => setActiveTab("Contact")}>Contact</li>
        </ul>

        {/* Conditional Addendum */}
        {activeTab() === "FAQ" && (
          <div style={{ marginTop: "16px" }}>
            <h3>FAQ Index</h3>
            <ul>
              {faqIndex.map((item) => (
                <li>{item}</li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        )}
      </aside>

      {/* Main Content */}
      <main style={{ flex: 1, padding: "16px" }}>
        {activeTab() === "Home" && <h1>Welcome to the Home Page</h1>}
        {activeTab() === "FAQ" && <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>}
        {activeTab() === "Contact" && <h1>Contact Us</h1>}
      </main>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

### Key Changes:
1. **Conditional Addendum**:
   - The FAQ index is appended to the sidebar if the `activeTab` signal is set to `"FAQ"`.
   - The `div` containing the FAQ index is rendered below the static menu in the sidebar using a `marginTop` for visual separation.

   ```javascript
   {activeTab() === "FAQ" && (
     <div style={{ marginTop: "16px" }}>
       <h3>FAQ Index</h3>
       <ul>
         {faqIndex.map((item) => (
           <li>{item}</li>
         ))}
       </ul>
     </div>
   )}
   ```

2. **Styling**:
   - Added padding and margin to keep the sidebar layout clean and visually distinct.

3. **Dynamic Behavior**:
   - The sidebar always displays the navigation links (`Home`, `FAQ`, `Contact`), and the FAQ index is appended only when `activeTab` is `"FAQ"`.

This approach ensures that the FAQ index acts as an "addendum" to the sidebar rather than replacing its content. Let me know if you'd like further refinements!

